OL,3,CLearning disabilities service could
OL,4,Cbecome blueprint to save NHS billions
OL,6,FA learning disabilities service in the
OL,7,FNorth West could become a blueprint to
OL,8,Fsave billions for the NHS - by keeping
OL,9,Fthose in a crisis out of hospital.
OL,11,FRadcliffe Place in Bury is the UK's
OL,12,Fonly residential assessment unit which
OL,13,Fsupports young people aged 16 to 25
OL,14,Fwith learning disabilities in
OL,15,Femergency situations.
OL,17,FStaff work tirelessly to support those
OL,18,Fwith complex needs who would often
OL,19,Finstead be admitted to hospital when
OL,20,Fit is not necessary.
