OL,3,CLearning disabilities service could
OL,4,Cbecome blueprint to save NHS billions
OL,6,FInstead of going onto hospital wards,
OL,7,Fpatients are assessed for 12 weeks and
OL,8,Fhave one-to-one care and therapy.
OL,10,FLauren, 23, is a patient at Radcliffe
OL,11,FPlace. She is autistic, has ADHD and a
OL,12,Fpossible learning disability,
OL,13,Fstruggles to express herself.
OL,15,F"I was isolated before I came here,"
OL,16,FLauren said. "I didn't feel like I was
OL,17,Fpart of society. I was a bit lonely
OL,18,Fand sad."
