OL,3,CLearning disabilities service could
OL,4,Cbecome blueprint to save NHS billions
OL,6,FSonny is 18, has learning disabilities
OL,7,Fand is severely autistic. His
OL,8,Fbehaviour can be challenging and he's
OL,9,Fbeen hospitalised on multiple
OL,10,Foccasions. When he has a crisis A&E is
OL,11,Foften the only option.
OL,13,FHis father, Patrick Moroney, said:
OL,14,F"One time we went to A&E and we were
OL,15,Fthere about 11 and a half hours before
OL,16,Fwe saw anybody and Sonny proceeded to
OL,17,Fsmash things up.
OL,19,F"They put us in offices...where he
OL,20,Fpicked the computers up over his head
OL,21,Fand smashed them."
OL,26,@vD@AOU}D@RO]
